description:
A MAN’S QUEST FOR HIS PAST AND HIS IDENTITY!

A man washes ashore—barely alive, a bullet hole in his head. On his shoulder, a tattoo of the Roman number XIII. And not a single memory of who he was, or how he got there. No sooner has he been nursed back to his feet by kind rescuers than armed goons track him down and attempt to kill him. Relentlessly pursued by assassins and secret agents, the man known as XIII begins a long quest to explore his past and recover his identity… From a presidential assassination to a coup d’état in South America; from a deadly conspiracy within the corridors of Washington DC to a break-out from a high-security prison for the criminally insane; through an ever increasing list of aliases… XIII will forge on against formidable odds and powerful, merciless opponents, until he knows, at last, who he is.

English reprinting of XIII. Published in the UK by Cinebook.
name: XIII

description:
The war has begun! Whose side will you be on? In the ‘Winter War’ during the winter of 1939 and 1940, Corporal Tero Toivanen serves his homeland of Finland against the Soviet Red Army. Tero is a sniper, and although he’s a veteran of his country’s military, like all able young men, he has never seen war. This changes quickly as he’s plunged directly into the fighting, where he sees plenty of death and destruction. As he moves through the bloody battles, he goes from skilled marksman to a cold-blooded killer. The Soviets press their advantage in armament and numbers, while Tero tries to keep himself and his young comrades alive.

Collected in Winter War.
name: Winter War

description:
This crime series is created by Michael and John Schwarz of Full Clip Productions, and written by Eisner Award-winner David Lapham (Stray Bullets). Damaged is illustrated by Leonardo Manco (Hellblazer) with cover art by acclaimed artist Alex Maleev.

Damaged tells of the story of two brothers, Frank and Henry Lincoln, long estranged after a violent event in their shared past forces them apart. Over the course of 35 years, the brothers pursue separate paths to enforce justice…. Frank, an upright citizen, becomes a distinguished veteran of the San Francisco police department, while Henry, a hardened vigilante, enforces the sort of justice the law is not allowed to. As the brothers approach retirement, each attempts to train a younger protégé in his image to take on the mafia underworld that corrupts the city by the bay. Sparks fly as the same crime scene and political powers bring the two brothers face to face on different sides of the law.
name: Damaged

description: Tom Whalen is a bad cop. Corrupt, strung out and under investigation by Internal Affairs, he's about to go down for the count. But when a drug deal goes bad, he wakes up in Bellevue with a police chaplain by his bed, offering him a last chance at redemption: join a secret unit of the NYPD that no one knew existed, protecting the city from the things no one believes exists. Irish banshees, Jewish Golems, Voodoo zombies... the superstitions of all the immigrant groups who ever passed through New York City are real, and the only thing between them and the unsuspecting people of New York is Tom Whalen and a very unique team of cops. But the forces of darkness are gathering, and Tom Whalen is about to discover that the greatest battle he ever fought will be the battle for his immortal soul.
name: Haunted City

description:
Published by the German wing of Panini Comics.


Plot: Darker than Black follows Hei, a Contractor who works for an organization known as "The Syndicate" as he tries to unlock the secrets of the Heaven's and Hell's Gates and his sisters disappearance.


Prologue:

Ten years prior to the events of Darker than Black, an unexplainable event occurred. This event gave birth to two mysterious territories that resided in South America and Japan. They were named the "Heaven's" and "Hell's Gates". These areas are so toxic that no ordinary life form could survive in them. Because of this, walls were erected around them in order to keep people from getting in and the dangers of the gate from getting out. The landscape wasn't the only thing that was affected. Following the event, the stars had disappeared and instead, were replaced by false ones. At this time, people known as Contractors began appearing. These Contractors are people with unique abilities. Added in with their cold nature and rational thinking, Contractors were often used as spies, or special units for governments and organizations, but were kept secret from the general public. Each false star in the sky correlates with each and every Contractor.

Five years after the event, the Heaven's Gate suddenly vanished. The reason for this remains unknown, however, some speculate that although it's physically gone, the Heaven's Gate still exists.
name: Darker Than Black
